obo:RO_0002333  a  owl:ObjectProperty .

gomodel:SYNGO_5308  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 2: FGF22 knockout mice have impaired synapse maturation/differentiation.\n\nFigure 3a-d: \"Overexpression of FGF22 and FGF7 in cultured hippocampal neurons leads to an increase in the clustering of VGLUT1 and VGAT puncta, respectively, on the FGF-expressing neuron (Fig. 3a). This suggests that FGF22 and FGF7 specifically promote differentiation of glutamatergic and GABAergic presynaptic terminals, respectively, as target-derived molecules.\"\n\nFigure 3e-j: immunofluorescence imaging of FGF22 in cultured hippocampal neurons showed co-localization with excitatory postsynapse marker protein PSD95 (DLG4). Same results for both overexpressed FGF22-EGFP and endogenous FGF22. FGF22 did not colocalize with inhibitory synapse marker proteins.. Experimental description: M&M: \"Dissociated hippocampal cultures were prepared from E16.5-P0 WT, FGF22KO and FGF7KO mice as previously described\"\n\nantibody:\nanti-FGF7 (1:100; Santa Cruz, H-73 and C-19)" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" ;
        dc:date           "2023-03-11" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_5308" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

